Amazon OpenSearch is successor to Amazon ElasticSearch
In Dynamo DB queries only exist by primnary key or indexes
with openSearch you can search any field even partially matches
its common to use OpenSearch as a complement to another database
two modes: managed cluster or serverless cluster
Does not nativley support SQL 
ingestion from data firehose, IoT, and CLoudwatch logs
security through cognito, IAM, KMS Encryption TLS
Comes with OpenSearch dashboards

-----------------------

DynamoDB ----> DynamoDB stream ---> Lambda Function ---> OpenSearch

